        "intro": "If your parent pays their own heating costs and has limited income, Alaska's Energy Assistance program can send a one-time payment directly to their heating company or utility provider. The payment amount varies based on household income, size, location, and heating type — but could significantly reduce winter utility bills.\n\nYour parent doesn't need to be 60+ to qualify, but seniors get priority for processing. The key requirement: they must pay at least $200 per year in out-of-pocket heating costs. Because funding is limited each year, applications often close early when money runs out — typically between October and August.\n\nIf your parent is enrolled in an Alaska Native tribe, they may need to apply through their tribal agency instead of the state. Non-tribal members apply through Alaska's Division of Public Assistance offices.",
