        "intro": "If you're already living with and caring for a parent who has Alzheimer's or dementia, Missouri's Structured Family Caregiving Waiver can turn your unpaid caregiving into paid employment. The state pays a caregiving agency, which then employs you to provide the hands-on care you're already giving — bathing, dressing, medication management, and daily support.\n\nThis isn't a program to hire new caregivers. Your parent must already live full-time in your household, have a confirmed dementia diagnosis from a Missouri doctor, and qualify for Medicaid. Because the program requires nursing-home-level care needs, your parent must need significant daily help with basic activities like eating, toileting, or getting dressed.\n\nThe state designed this as a cost-effective alternative to nursing facility placement, allowing families to keep their loved ones at home while receiving compensation for the intensive care required.",
