            "question": "Can my spouse with dementia qualify if I'm already their caregiver?",
            "answer": "Yes, spouses can be primary caregivers under this program. Your spouse must meet all other requirements — dementia diagnosis, nursing facility level of care, and Medicaid eligibility. The caregiving agency will employ you to provide the care you're already giving."
