        "intro": "If you're living with and caring for a parent who needs daily help with bathing, dressing, or staying safe at home, Nevada's Respite Care Voucher program provides up to $1,000 annually to pay for professional caregiver relief. Because you qualify regardless of your parent's income or assets, this program focuses on functional need — your parent must require supervision or assistance with multiple daily activities and be at risk when left alone.\n\nThe vouchers reimburse you for hiring professional respite care or agency services, giving you time to work, run errands, or simply rest. Because funding comes from state grants with limited availability, applications go through a selection process rather than automatic approval. Only available in Northern Nevada through Carson City and south to Tonopah.",
