      "quickFacts": [
        "Vermont's Senior Companion Program volunteers earn $4/hour, making it one of the few programs that can provide income while helping seniors",
        "Most Vermont senior services are coordinated through five Area Agencies on Aging that cover different regions of the state",
        "Vermont's rural geography means some programs have waiting lists or limited availability outside of Burlington and Montpelier areas"
      ],
      "resourcesVsBenefits": "Vermont's approach emphasizes volunteer-based resources over cash benefits — programs like the Senior Companion Program are available regardless of your parent's income, focusing on community support rather than financial qualification. This means your parent can access companionship and practical help even if their income is too high for federal benefit programs, but it also means fewer direct financial assistance options than states with more extensive benefit programs."
