        "geographicScope": {
          "type": "state",
          "stateVariation": false
        },
        "intro": "If your parent needs help with bathing, dressing, or getting around but doesn't require nursing home care, Medicaid Personal Care can provide paid caregivers in their home. This Washington program covers personal care assistance with daily activities — without the strict nursing facility requirements of other Medicaid programs.\n\nYour parent must need either extensive help with one daily activity OR some help with at least three activities like bathing, dressing, toileting, transferring, or mobility. The program serves low-income Washington residents regardless of age through one of five regional health plans.\n\nUnlike nursing home Medicaid, MPC specifically excludes people who need nursing facility level care — it fills the gap for those who need personal assistance but can remain in community settings like their home, adult family homes, or assisted living facilities.",
